**AUTOSAVE TO LOCALSTORAGE** (debounced — survives reloads):
```javascript
let saveTimer = null;
function queueSave() {
  clearTimeout(saveTimer);
  saveTimer = setTimeout(() => {
    localStorage.setItem('editor-draft', editor.value);
  }, 500);
}
editor.addEventListener('input', queueSave);
// Restore on load
editor.value = localStorage.getItem('editor-draft') || '';
updateCounts(); if (window.marked) renderPreview();
```

**RULES:**
- Always use `setRangeText(..., 'select')` for toolbar wraps — it preserves undo history (vs. `value =` which destroys it).
- For line-prefix actions (heading, list, todo, blockquote), expand selection to full lines first — partial-line prefixes look broken.
- Provide keyboard shortcuts for bold/italic/link — users will try Cmd+B and feel a missing dependency.
- Use `textContent` or `marked.parse(...)` — never `innerHTML` of raw user text.
- Tab-size on the textarea: 2 (modern web default; 4 only if it's clearly code).
- Word counter: split on `/\s+/` after `trim()` — don't split a string with a leading space and report `+1`.
- Don't pull Prism unless syntax highlighting is actually needed — adds 50KB+.
- Marked.js is 25KB, worth it for live preview; for static rendering, server-side render markdown instead.
